The development, test, staging, and production environments for DEX;

All software running in these environments;

Specialized software needed to develop and test these systems;

Relevant documentation.

All products generated both paper and digital, are to be considered as Controlled Unclassified Information (CUI) and will remain the property of the government. The cloud environment and any systems, documentation and tools that exists in this environment will be transitioned to the government and/or subsequent vendor (if any) at the completion of this contract.

Appendix A: DEX Role Descriptions

Technical Product Manager: Represent the voice of the end-user to their team. Manages the daily activities of the agile development team and facilitates the improvement of development culture. Leads one or more multi-disciplinary agile delivery teams to deliver excellent new products and/or iterations to existing products to meet user needs. Has a strong technical background that enables this person to write software specifications, prioritize technical work, and "hang" in highly technical conversations with engineers. Makes tradeoffs between the needs of users, the business, and the technology. Experienced in software delivery, building roadmaps, scoping releases, and developing success metrics. Ensures tactical delivery and execution of software development. 

Product Manager: Represent the voice of the end-user to their team. Manages the daily activities of the agile development team and facilitates the improvement of development culture. Leads one or more multi-disciplinary agile delivery teams to deliver excellent new products and/or iterations to existing products to meet user needs. Has a strong understanding of the user and the business. Makes tradeoffs between the needs of users, the business, and the technology. Experienced in software delivery, building roadmaps, scoping releases, and developing success metrics. Ensures tactical delivery and execution of software development. 

UX Researcher: Strategizes, designs and executes qualitative and quantitative user research in collaboration with a multidisciplinary team including design, research, product, and engineering. Coordinates research strategy and activities that map to medium and long-term product and engineering objectives. Functions as a usability advocate across applications, services, and teams by emphasizing research and design principles that are people-first. Works with designers to plan, facilitate and analyze user-facing concepts, products, or features through usability testing or other methods. Responsible for planning and implementing user research activities, collecting and synthesizing qualitative and quantitative data, translating research into insights, and making recommendations.
